ta source.\",\n108:         \"The target keeps seeded content repositories permission-free in phase-02 and adds no request-permission scaffolding.\",\n109:         \"The HarmonyOS routing shell keeps the same route/shell scope without permission prompts, and `entry/src/main/module.json5::requestPermissions` remains empty.\",\n110:         \"`session_repository.cj` preserves the same shared in-memory state responsibilities without any permission prompt or protected-access flow.\",\n111:         \"`login_preferences_service.cj` persists login state through `Preferences` without any permission prompt or protected-access flow.\",\n112:         \"`LoginPreferencesService` preserves the same single-file single-key login preference contract and exposes read/write/toggle helpers over HarmonyOS `Preferences`.\",\n113:         \"`LoginPreferencesService` preserves the same persisted login-state contract, and phase-02 startup/login/profile consumers only need immediate reads or writes at route boundaries rather than a long-lived observer subscription.\",\n114:         \"`LoginPreferencesService.toggleLoginState()` and the login/profile stores preserve the same persisted session flip behavior for startup, login success, and logout.\",\n115:         \"The target keeps repository/service wiring permission-free for phase-02 startup/session/navigation.\",\n116:         \"`home_content_repository.cj` keeps catalogue loading fully in-memory and permission-free in phase-02.\",\n117:         \"`SessionRepository` preserves the same shared state responsibilities without any permission prompt or protected-access flow.\",\n118:         \"`LoginPreferencesService` keeps login persistence inside HarmonyOS `Preferences` without adding any permission prompt or protected-access flow.\",\n119:         \"`LoginPreferencesService` preserves the same persisted login-state source of truth, and `StartupLaunchService`, `loginStore`, and `profileStore` reuse that shared state at the same startup/login/logout boundaries that the current-phase source observes throu...\",\n120:         \"`LoginPreferencesService.readLoginState(context)` reads the same persisted login flag that startup uses to choose onboarding or home.\",\n121:         \"`LoginPreferencesService.toggleLoginState()` preserves the same persisted session flip behavior reused by startup, login success, and logout flows.\"\n122:       ],\n123:       \"acceptanceEvidence\": [\n124:         \"Replace broad endpoints with precise target functions, types, resources, or tests before closing the group.\"\n125:       ],\n126:       \"riskHints\": [\n127:         \"current evidence uses broad shell/root/whole-file endpoints\"\n128:       ],\n129:       \"matrixRows\": [\n130:         {\n131:           \"kind\": \"source-feature\",\n132:           \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-data-data-source-f-f170137f2d-001-file-document-storage-saf-mediastore-or\",\n133:           \"featureName\": \"File, document, storage, SAF, MediaStore, or import/export behavior.\",\n134:           \"sourcePath\": \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/data/data_source/FakeData.kt\",\n135:           \"importance\": \"critical\",\n136:           \"plannedPhase\": \"phase-02-startup-session-navigation\",\n137:           \"status\": \"not-applicable\",\n138:           \"parityLevel\": \"not-applicable\",\n139:           \"verdict\": \"complete\",\n140:           \"reasons\": [\n141:             \"not-applicable has source/notes explanation\"\n142:           ],\n143:           \"targetEndpoints\": [\n144:             \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/content/home_content_repository.cj\",\n145:             \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/session_repository.cj\"\n146:           ],\n147:           \"tests\": [\n148:             \"entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_repository_contract_test.cj\",\n149:             \"blocked: cjpm test (entry/src/test/cangjie)\"\n150:           